The localized states can be formed in the shape of tails over the valence band edge (EV) or/and below conduction band edge (EC) of NiO as in Fig. 2(c) due to the crystal disorder28. These energy states can participate in light absorption, being expressed by Urbach energy. The Urbach energy, EU can be expressed as below29,30,4α(E)=Cexp(EEU)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
